ident of Taylor Ramsey Corporation  a lumber products manufacturing company  headquartered in Lynchburg  Virginia  Mr  Ramsey is involved in numerous organizations in Lynchburg  He has served on the Board and as Chairman of James River Day School  a private elementary day school  as a member of the Board of Advisors of the Lynchburg College School of Business  and as a member of the Board of Junior Achievement of Lynchburg  Mr  Ramsey served as Chairman of the Virginia Aviation Board  1994 2003  a gubernatorial appointment  where he was responsible for advising the Governor of Virginia  the Secretary of Transportation  and the Director of Aviation on all matters relating to aviation in the Commonwealth of Virginia  He was a member of the board of the local hospital s foundation and was a member and President of the Board of Boonsboro Country Club  He was also on the Board of Cooperative Savings   Loan prior to its merger with a national bank  He currently serves on the AAA Mid Atlantic Virginia Regional Board  Mr  Ramsey received a B S  in biology from Virginia Military Institute in 1972  While a cadet  he earned monograms in both football and track  In football  he earned first team All State  All Big 5  All Southern Conference  and Honorable Mention All American honors  He was Co captain of the football team his senior year  In 2005 he was inducted into the VMI Sports Hall of Fame  In addition he was named to the Dean s List several times and achieved the rank of lieutenant in the Corps of Cadets  Mr  Ramsey has been active in the Virginia Military Institute alumni organizations since his graduation  He has served on the Board of Governors of the VMI Keydet Club  1991 1996  as a member of the VMI Athletic Council  1993 2001  and on the Board of Trustees of the VMI Foundation  1999 2007  and as President of The VMI Foundation  2004 2007  He currently serves on the VMI Foundation Investment Committee  Mr  Ramsey and his wife  Margaret  live at Smith Mountain Lake  Virginia and have four grown children and six grandchildren  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 